{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea13355b-bbed-4f46-8c1c-528fe67fd9fe","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2**, you can inject `TestContext` via the constructor and use `async Task` lifecycle methods. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service = null!;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task Setup()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test cleanup\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task Teardown()\n    {\n        await _service.DisposeAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed as a constructor parameter (MSTest v3+). No need for `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** can return `async Task` for async setup.\n- **`[TestCleanup]`** can also be `async Task`.\n- For **class-level** async init, use `[ClassInitialize]` with `static async Task`.\n- The old property-injection style still works but constructor injection is preferred.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f37fb2b-2be5-4da9-b00b-c6818ffb932d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), `TestContext` can be injected via the constructor, and you can use `[ClassInitialize]`/`[TestInitialize]` for sync init and implement `IAsyncInit` or use async lifecycle methods. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended approach is:\n1. Constructor injection for `TestContext`\n2. `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` for per-test sync setup/teardown\n3. These methods can be `async Task` for async initialization\n\n\nNow I'll put together a concrete example showing how to structure this properly.","outputTokens":557,"requestId":"A02E:147A9A:407D911:44C748F:6A034CD7"},"id":"91f72312-250a-4fae-814d-efc9aa3252ef","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:53:07.192Z","parentId":"10a54727-f9d6-49d8-8392-6ee2acee455b"}
